#Approach:

Longest Subarray with Sum K – Prefix Sum + HashMap Approach

Is problem me hum prefix sum use karte hain.
Hum running sum calculate karte hain aur HashMap me store karte hain
ki kaunsa sum kis index par pehli baar aaya tha.

Agar kisi index par current sum - k map me mil jata hai,
to iska matlab beech ka subarray ka sum k hai.
Us subarray ki length nikalte hain using current index - stored index
aur max length update karte hain.

Important:
Map me hamesha prefix sum ka first occurrence store karna hai,
kyunki hume longest subarray chahiye.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:
class Solution {
    public int longestSubarray(int[] nums, int k) {
       HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
       int sum = 0;
       int maxLen = 0;

       for(int i=0; i<nums.length; i++){
           sum += nums[i];
           if(sum == k){
            maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, i+1);
           }

           int rem = sum - k;

           if(map.containsKey(rem)){
            int len = i - map.get(rem);
            maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, len);
           }

           if(!map.containsKey(sum)){
            map.put(sum, i);
           }
       }
       return maxLen;
    }
}
